<item>
            <title>[LU-11332] Lustre quota issue</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11332</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hi all,&lt;br/&gt;
i have a little problem with quota of Lustre fileystem and samba.&lt;br/&gt;
Sometimes, when users delete files from windows client using samba, the files are deleted but quota remain exactly the same without decreses.&lt;br/&gt;
The solution to correct this problem seems to be only a reboot of Lustre hosts.&lt;br/&gt;
Do you have any idea to resolve this problem or correct quota without restart Lustre?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Lustre Version:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;lustre: 2.6.0&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: patchless_client&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;build: 2.6.0-RC2--PRISTINE-2.6.32-431.20.3.el6_lustre.x86_64&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Samba is provided from a cluster of two server with CTDB cluter:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;SMBD Version: 3.6.23-36.el6_8&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;CTDB Version: 2.5.6&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
